//
// T037: `nsl-fmt -i` rewrites the file in place (atomic write-to-
// temp + rename per FR-002). Verifies the file's bytes after the
// operation. At Phase 3a-CLI the formatter is byte-passthrough so
// the file content is unchanged; the test still proves the rename
// path executes.

// RUN: printf 'module foo {}\n' > %t.nsl
// RUN: nsl-fmt -i %t.nsl
// RUN: FileCheck %s < %t.nsl
// CHECK: module foo {}
